From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] brush-core: clear_all_handlers - a fresh shell inherits no
 traps

A real `sh script` is a fresh process with NO trap handlers; the engine's
in-process snoop clones the calling shell (traps included) and must be able
to reset them wholesale. configure's EXIT trap (`rm -f -r conftest* ...`)
firing at every snooped child's exit deleted files the caller had just
generated.

---
diff --git a/src/traps.rs b/src/traps.rs
index e432488..a18ec3b 100644
--- a/src/traps.rs
+++ b/src/traps.rs
@@ -224,6 +224,13 @@ impl TrapHandlerConfig {
         );
     }
 
+    /// Removes ALL registered trap handlers — a freshly exec'd shell (a
+    /// snooped `sh script` running in-process) starts with no traps, unlike
+    /// a subshell clone.
+    pub fn clear_all_handlers(&mut self) {
+        self.handlers.clear();
+    }
+
     /// Removes handlers for a trap signal.
     ///
     /// # Arguments
